26/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The opposition Serbian Progressive Party (SNS) will hold an anti-government rally in Belgrade on February 4th, SNS Vice President Aleksandar Vucic announced on Friday (December 24th). 
Vucic said at a press conference that his party will try to drum up support for the rally among other opposition parties. 
New Serbia says it will participate, while the Democratic Party of Serbia and the Serbian Radical Party have declined. 
The SNS blames the ruling coalition for the economy and rising unemployment. 
(RTS, Tanjug, Politika, Beta, B92 - 24/12/10)
